body:
As far as the system is concerned (and it&#039;s the community that decides what&#039;s acceptable and not by what they choose to report), defending yourself is fine, but retaliation is not. This doesn&#039;t make any sense. The toxic players who are reporting him shouldn&#039;t get to decide what&#039;s acceptable and if anything aren&#039;t classed as members of our community anymore.

-Yes, people should ignore/mute instead of retaliation, BUT retaliation is almost the same as defending yourself. It&#039;s sad how you&#039;re considering toxic players reports against innocent victims. Fueling a toxic player is your excuse for making the situation worse, the match is already ruined having the toxic person playing on the same rift in the first place. The fun is already over for everyone. The damage is done, him retaliating is only a result in the toxic community.

-What i&#039;m trying to say is stop punishing the innocent it&#039;s only going to create more toxicity in the community. You think that you&#039;re solving it but you&#039;re actually fueling the fire even more. It&#039;s a domino effect, many players get pissed off being punished unfairly and then go on to being toxic trolls venting out their frustration on others, THEN the player victims of them retaliate = get a punishment, so on and so forth. {{champion:89}}  {{item:3190}}
